            <!-- Dev Console (target for devconsoleTab.js) -->
            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="devconsole" role="tabpanel"></div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="compiler" role="tabpanel">
                <h3>HTML App Compiler</h3>
                <p>This tool compiles your loaded HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files into a single standalone HTML file,
                    using the latest content from the editor.</p>
                <div id="compiler-content" class="mb-2">
                    <div class="form-inline mb-2">
                        <label for="compile-filename" class="mr-2">Output filename</label>
                        <input id="compile-filename" type="text" class="form-control form-control-sm mr-2"
                            placeholder="defaults to folder name">
                        <small class="text-muted">If no extension is given, .html is added</small>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check mb-2">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="minify-output">
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="minify-output">Minify HTML output</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check mb-1">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="include-devconsole">
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="include-devconsole">Include Dev Console scripts
                            (devconsole.js)</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check mb-2">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="include-test-recorder">
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="include-test-recorder">Include Test Recorder script
                            (testRecorder.js)</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check mb-2">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="inline-cdn" checked>
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="inline-cdn">Inline external CDN resources (recommended for
                            offline security)</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check mb-2">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="add-security-headers" checked>
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="add-security-headers">Add security headers (restricts
                            network connections)</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check mb-1">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="allow-asksage-api">
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="allow-asksage-api">Allow Ask Sage API (CAPRA)</label>
                    </div>
                    <small class="text-muted d-block mb-1">Adds <code>api.capra.flankspeed.us.navy.mil</code> to
                        <code>connect-src</code> for Ask Sage usage.</small>
                    <div class="form-check mb-1">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="allow-genaimil-api">
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="allow-genaimil-api">Allow GenAI.mil API</label>
                    </div>
                    <small class="text-muted d-block mb-2">Adds <code>api.genai.mil</code> to <code>connect-src</code> for GenAI.mil usage.</small>
	                    <div class="mb-2">
	                        <label for="security-connect-allowlist" class="form-label mb-1">Additional API allowlist (optional, connect-src)</label>
	                        <textarea id="security-connect-allowlist" class="form-control form-control-sm" rows="2"
	                            placeholder="One host/origin per line or comma. Example: api.openai.com, api.anthropic.com, api.genai.mil"></textarea>
	                        <small class="text-muted">Leave blank for strict offline mode unless one of the API checkboxes above is enabled (<code>connect-src 'none'</code>). Entries are normalized to host/origin and paths are ignored. First outbound API use will prompt for user approval in the isolated shell.</small>
	                    </div>
	                    <div class="form-check mb-1">
	                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="sharepoint-compat-mode">
	                        <label class="form-check-label" for="sharepoint-compat-mode">SharePoint/SPFx API compatibility mode</label>
	                    </div>
	                    <div class="mb-2">
	                        <label for="sharepoint-site-url" class="form-label mb-1">SharePoint site URL (used when compatibility mode is enabled)</label>
	                        <input id="sharepoint-site-url" type="url" class="form-control form-control-sm" value="https://flankspeed.sharepoint-mil.us/sites/prometheus" placeholder="https://tenant.sharepoint.mil/sites/YourSite" disabled>
	                        <small class="text-muted">Keeps security headers and runtime wrapper. Adds <code>'self'</code> and this SharePoint origin to <code>connect-src</code>, and allows SharePoint-origin bridge/API requests with query params.</small>
	                    </div>
	                    <div class="form-check mb-1">
	                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="allow-cdn-pulldowns">
	                        <label class="form-check-label" for="allow-cdn-pulldowns">Allow CDN pull-downs for compiler inlining</label>
	                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-2">
                        <label for="security-cdn-allowlist" class="form-label mb-1">CDN allowlist (optional, used only when enabled above)</label>
                        <textarea id="security-cdn-allowlist" class="form-control form-control-sm" rows="3">https://code.jquery.com
https://cdn.jsdelivr.net
https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com
https://unpkg.com
https://esm.sh
https://cdn.skypack.dev
https://jspm.dev
https://cdn.tailwindcss.com</textarea>
                        <small class="text-muted">Unchecked by default. When enabled, these CDN origins are added to <code>connect-src</code> so compiled Forge can download external resources during compile/inlining. For these CDN origins, requests with query params (<code>?</code>) or fragments (<code>#</code>) are blocked; path-based URLs are allowed.</small>
                    </div>
                    <small class="text-muted d-block mb-2">Unchecked: compiler comments out these debug scripts by
                        default. Security headers and CDN inlining help ensure offline-only operation.</small>
                    <button id="compileButton" class="btn btn-primary">Compile Project</button>
                </div>
                <div id="compiler-results"></div>
                <div class="mt-3 p-2" style="background:#141c26; border:1px solid #232e3b; border-radius:8px;">
                    <h5>Hash Verification</h5>
                    <p class="mb-1"><small>Upload a compiled HTML to verify against <code>compiled-hashes.csv</code> in
                            the loaded project.</small></p>
                    <div class="form-inline mb-2">
                        <input type="file" id="hash-verify-file" accept=".html,.htm" class="form-control-file mr-2" />
                        <button id="hash-verify-btn" class="btn btn-secondary">Verify Hash</button>
                    </div>
                    <div id="hash-verify-result"></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="decompiler" role="tabpanel">
                <h3>Decompiler</h3>
                <p>Load a compiled HTML created by the HTML Compiler. The decompiler reads an embedded manifest and
                    reconstructs original files and references.</p>
                <div class="mb-2">
                    <input type="file" id="decompile-file" accept=".html,.htm" />
                    <button id="decompile-analyze" class="btn btn-secondary">Analyze</button>
                    <button id="decompile-write" class="btn btn-primary" disabled>Write Files...</button>
                </div>
                <div id="decompile-results" class="p-2"
                    style="background:#141c26; border:1px solid #232e3b; border-radius:8px; min-height: 60px;"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="llm-formatter" role="tabpanel">
                <h3>Filtered File Concatenator for LLMs</h3>
                <p>This tool parses your selected HTML entry point to find referenced files. Select files to include,
                    then generate and copy context for your AI chat.</p>
                <button id="generateContextButton" class="btn btn-primary">Generate LLM Context</button>
                <div id="llm-entrypoint-wrap" class="mt-2 mb-2" style="display:none;">
                    <label for="llm-entrypoint-select" class="form-label mb-1">HTML entry point</label>
                    <select id="llm-entrypoint-select" class="form-select form-select-sm" style="max-width: 420px;"></select>
                </div>
                <div id="checkboxContainer"></div>
                <button id="updateButton" style="display:none;" class="btn btn-secondary mt-2">Generate + Copy</button>
                <div id="llm-output-controls" style="display:none;">
                    <h2>Generation Status</h2>
                    <div id="text-stats" class="mb-2 p-2"
                        style="background-color: #0e1419; border: 1px solid #232e3b; border-radius: 8px;">
                        <strong>Statistics:</strong>
                        <span id="char-count">0 characters</span> |
                        <span id="size-display">0 KB</span> |
                        <span id="token-count">~0 tokens</span>
                    </div>
                    <button id="copyButton" class="btn btn-info">Copy Again</button>
                    <p id="llm-copy-status" class="mt-2 mb-0 text-info small"></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="test-recorder" role="tabpanel"></div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="math-logic-tester" role="tabpanel"></div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="sharedrive-nosql" role="tabpanel">
                <!-- Content will be injected by sharedriveNosqlTab.js -->
            </div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="ai-helper" role="tabpanel">
                <h3>Brainstorm</h3>
                <p class="prompt-panel-copy">Generate prompts for discovering needs, shaping a concept, and planning a new app.
                    <strong>Important:</strong> each step is stateless, so paste the right context into that row before generating the next prompt.</p>

                <div class="table-responsive brainstorm-table-wrap">
                    <table class="table table-dark table-striped table-hover mb-0 brainstorm-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th style="width: 20%;">Step</th>
                                <th style="width: 28%;">What It Does</th>
                                <th>Your Context + Generated Prompt</th>
                                <th style="width: 170px;">Generate</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr id="ai-step1">
                                <td>
                                    <strong>JTBD Interview</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 1</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <div class="step-summary">Creates an interview prompt that makes the AI question you like a researcher instead of jumping to solutions.</div>
                                    <div class="step-usage">Use this first when the problem is still fuzzy or you want better requirements.</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <textarea id="ai-ctx1" class="form-control" rows="4"
                                        placeholder="e.g., I'm frustrated with how hard it is to track maintenance requests..."></textarea>
                                    <div class="prompt-output p-3 rounded" id="ai-out1"
                                        style="font-family: monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"></div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm w-100" data-ai-action="generate-and-copy"
                                        data-ai-step="1">Generate + Copy</button>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr id="ai-step2">
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Jobs + Tool Ideas</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 2</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <div class="step-summary">Turns a short JTBD summary into candidate jobs and multiple tool ideas for each one.</div>
                                    <div class="step-usage">Use this after the interview once you want a clean list of problem statements and solution directions.</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <textarea id="ai-ctx2" class="form-control" rows="4"
                                        placeholder="e.g., Summary: User struggles with X..."></textarea>
                                    <div class="prompt-output p-3 rounded" id="ai-out2"
                                        style="font-family: monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"></div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm w-100" data-ai-action="generate-and-copy"
                                        data-ai-step="2">Generate + Copy</button>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr id="ai-step3">
                                <td>
                                    <strong>MVP Ladder</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 3</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <div class="step-summary">Builds a five-stage MVP ladder so you can validate the riskiest assumption before overbuilding.</div>
                                    <div class="step-usage">Use this when you already picked one job and one tool concept.</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <textarea id="ai-ctx3" class="form-control" rows="4"
                                        placeholder="e.g., Job: When ..., I want ... Tool: Static dashboard..."></textarea>
                                    <div class="prompt-output p-3 rounded" id="ai-out3"
                                        style="font-family: monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"></div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm w-100" data-ai-action="generate-and-copy"
                                        data-ai-step="3">Generate + Copy</button>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr id="ai-step4">
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Technical Approaches</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 4</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <div class="step-summary">Explores multiple implementation paths, tradeoffs, and offline constraints for the concept you selected.</div>
                                    <div class="step-usage">Use this before coding when you want to compare viable architectures.</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <textarea id="ai-ctx4" class="form-control" rows="4"
                                        placeholder="e.g., An application for drafting Post Mission Products..."></textarea>
                                    <div class="prompt-output p-3 rounded" id="ai-out4"
                                        style="font-family: monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"></div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm w-100" data-ai-action="generate-and-copy"
                                        data-ai-step="4">Generate + Copy</button>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr id="ai-step5">
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Build Prompt</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 5</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <div class="step-summary">Produces the final build-ready prompt for generating the first version of the app.</div>
                                    <div class="step-usage">Use this when the concept, scope, and constraints are settled and you want complete files back.</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <textarea id="ai-ctx5" class="form-control" rows="4"
                                        placeholder="e.g., Use localStorage to cache assets, include drag-and-drop demo module..."></textarea>
                                    <div class="prompt-output p-3 rounded" id="ai-out5"
                                        style="font-family: monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"></div>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm w-100" data-ai-action="generate-and-copy"
                                        data-ai-step="5">Generate + Copy</button>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-3 p-2 text-muted text-center" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
                    Each step is independent; copy/paste what you need forward. All processing happens locally.
                    Customize templates in <code>aiHelper.js</code>.
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- ADVANCED PROMPTS - Separate Tab -->
            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="ai-advanced" role="tabpanel">
                <h3>Add Features</h3>
                <p class="mb-3">Choose a feature below to see what it adds, why it is useful, and when to use it. Click
                    <strong>Incorporate</strong> to generate a ready-to-paste prompt for your current codebase.</p>

                <div class="table-responsive advanced-feature-table-wrap">
                    <table class="table table-dark table-striped table-hover mb-0 advanced-feature-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th style="width: 24%;">Feature</th>
                                <th>Description, Rationale, and When to Use</th>
                                <th style="width: 140px;">Incorporate</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>JSON Save/Load</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 6</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Creates backup and restore controls so users can export app state to disk and reload it later. This reduces risk of data loss and makes handoff between users/systems simple. Use this for offline workflows, training tools, and any app where session continuity matters.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="6">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>CSV/Excel Import</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 7</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Adds structured ingestion from user spreadsheets so teams can move existing data into the app quickly without retyping. Use this when source data already lives in exports, trackers, or roster sheets and onboarding speed is important.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="7">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Document Export</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 8</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Generates formal deliverables from in-app data, helping users produce reports and brief-ready outputs directly from the workflow. Use this when teams need repeatable outputs for leadership updates, records, or external sharing.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="8">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>OCR (Image to Text)</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 9</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Extracts machine-editable text from photos and scanned documents, reducing manual transcription. Use this when field data arrives as images, handwritten notes, or screenshots and you need that content searchable or reusable in downstream logic.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="9">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>LLM JSON Pipeline</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 10</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Implements a controlled AI loop: app data becomes a structured prompt, AI returns JSON, app validates and visualizes results. Use this when you want AI-assisted analysis while keeping deterministic parsing and user-verifiable outputs.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="10">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>SharePoint List Integration</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 11</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Connects app state to SharePoint lists for enterprise persistence, collaboration, and governance. Use this when your deployment environment is SharePoint-based and you need centralized data with list permissions, auditability, and standard org workflows.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="11">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Capra/Ask Sage API Integration</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 12</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Adds a secure Ask Sage API workflow using the CAPRA endpoint pattern. Use this when your app must call Ask Sage while preserving Forge security compilation controls and explicit network approval.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="12">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>GenAI.mil API Integration</strong>
                                    <div class="feature-step">Step 13</div>
                                </td>
                                <td>Adds OpenAI-compatible GenAI.mil API calls using the documented <code>/v1/models</code> and <code>/v1/chat/completions</code> pattern. Use this when your app needs GenAI.mil chat completions with secure key handling and Forge security compilation controls.</td>
                                <td><button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-advanced-incorporate-step="13">Incorporate</button></td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-3 p-2 text-muted text-center" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
                    In <strong>Incorporate</strong>, you can optionally append codebase context when starting a new
                    conversation, matching the quick prompt workflow.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="live-preview" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="live-preview-tab">
                <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
                    <button id="lp-build-run" class="btn btn-primary mr-2">Build & Run</button>
                    <button id="lp-refresh" class="btn btn-secondary mr-2">Refresh</button>
                    <button id="lp-popout" class="btn btn-info mr-3">Pop Out</button>
                    <div class="form-check form-check-inline">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="lp-auto" />
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="lp-auto">Auto-rebuild on save</label>
                    </div>
                    <small class="ml-3 text-muted" id="lp-status">Idle</small>
                </div>
                <iframe id="live-preview-iframe" title="Live preview output"
                    sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-modals allow-downloads"></iframe>
                <div class="mt-3">
                    <h6 class="text-info mb-2">Preview build log</h6>
                    <div id="live-preview-log"></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="sast" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="sast-tab"></div>
            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="security-reviewer" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="security-reviewer-tab">
            </div>
            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="leaflet-map" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="leaflet-map-tab"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="agent-resize-handle" title="Resize Prometheus panel"></div>
    <aside id="right-panel" class="collapsed" aria-label="Prometheus panel">
        <!-- Header bar -->
        <div id="right-panel-header">
            <span class="athena-brand">
                <svg class="forge-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                    <rect x="3" y="4" width="10" height="8" rx="2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                    <circle cx="6.5" cy="8" r="0.9" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"></circle>
                    <circle cx="9.5" cy="8" r="0.9" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"></circle>
                    <path d="M8 2.3V4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                </svg>
                Prometheus
            </span>
            <span id="ai-provider-safety-chip" class="ai-provider-safety-chip" style="display:none"></span>
            <span id="ai-online-status" class="ai-online-dot unknown" title="Checking..."></span>
            <span id="ai-activity-indicator" class="ai-activity-dot idle" title="Idle"></span>
            <span id="ai-activity-label" class="ai-activity-label"></span>
            <div style="flex:1"></div>
            <button class="athena-header-btn" onclick="restartAthenaConversation()" title="New chat">
                <svg class="forge-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M8 3V13M3 8H13" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                </svg>
            </button>
            <div class="ai-history-wrapper">
                <button class="athena-header-btn" onclick="aiAgent.toggleHistoryDropdown()" title="Chat history">
                    <svg class="forge-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                        <circle cx="8" cy="8" r="5.2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></circle>
                        <path d="M8 5V8L10.3 9.4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
                    </svg>
                </button>
                <div id="ai-history-dropdown" class="ai-history-dropdown"></div>
            </div>
            <button class="athena-header-btn" id="athena-config-toggle" onclick="toggleAthenaConfig()" title="Settings">
                <svg class="forge-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                    <circle cx="8" cy="8" r="2.1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></circle>
                    <path d="M8 2.2V4M8 12V13.8M2.2 8H4M12 8H13.8M3.8 3.8L5 5M11 11L12.2 12.2M12.2 3.8L11 5M5 11L3.8 12.2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                </svg>
            </button>
            <button class="athena-header-btn" onclick="toggleRightPanel(false)" title="Close">
                <svg class="forge-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M4 4L12 12M12 4L4 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                </svg>
            </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Profile bar (rendered by JS) -->
        <div id="ai-profile-bar" class="ai-profile-bar"></div>
        <div id="ai-provider-safety-banner" class="ai-provider-safety-banner" style="display:none"></div>

        <div id="right-panel-content">
            <!-- Scrollable messages area -->
            <div id="ai-chat-messages"></div>

            <!-- Composer area (pinned to bottom) -->
            <div id="ai-composer">
                <div id="ai-attach-preview" class="ai-attach-preview" style="display:none"></div>
                <div id="ai-chat-input-row">
                    <input type="file" id="ai-attach-input" accept="image/*,.txt,.js,.html,.css,.json,.py,.md,.csv" style="display:none" onchange="aiAgent.handleAttachment(this)">
                    <div class="ai-input-wrap">
                        <textarea id="ai-chat-input" rows="2" placeholder="Ask Prometheus anything..." onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'&&!event.shiftKey){event.preventDefault();sendAIMessage()}" oninput="autoResizeAthenaInput(this)"></textarea>
                        <div class="ai-input-actions">
                            <button id="ai-chat-attach-btn" class="ai-input-icon-btn" onclick="openAIAttachPicker()" title="Attach file">
                                <svg class="ai-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <path d="M6 8.7L9.9 4.8A2.3 2.3 0 0 1 13.2 8L7.5 13.7A3.6 3.6 0 0 1 2.4 8.6L8.2 2.8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                            <button id="ai-chat-send-btn" class="ai-input-send-btn" onclick="sendAIMessage()" title="Send message">
                                <svg class="ai-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <path d="M2 8L14 2.5L11.2 13.5L7.4 8.6L2 8Z" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
                                    <path d="M7.4 8.6L14 2.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                                </svg>
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ai-input-extras">
                        <button id="ai-plan-execute-btn" class="btn btn-sm btn-success" style="display:none" onclick="aiAgent.approvePlan()" title="Execute pending plan"><svg class="ai-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 3.5L12 8L5 12.5Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg> Execute Plan</button>
                        <button id="ai-chat-stop" class="btn btn-sm" style="display:none" onclick="aiAgent.abort()"><svg class="ai-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="4.2" y="4.2" width="7.6" height="7.6" rx="1.2" fill="currentColor"></rect></svg> Stop</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div id="ai-agent-limits" class="ai-agent-limits">
                    <label title="Plan mode" class="ai-mode-toggle">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="ai-plan-mode" onchange="aiAgent.togglePlanMode(this.checked)">
                        <span id="plan-mode-label" class="plan-mode-label">Plan</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="ai-limits-sep"></div>
                    <label title="Auto-accept all code changes (creates safety checkpoint each prompt)" class="ai-mode-toggle">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="ai-auto-accept" onchange="aiAgent.toggleAutoAccept(this.checked)">
                        <span class="plan-mode-label">Auto</span>
                    </label>
                    <div class="ai-limits-sep"></div>
                    <label title="Max agentic steps">Steps <input id="ai-max-steps" type="number" value="25" min="1" max="200" onchange="aiAgent._applyLimits()"></label>
                    <label title="Timeout in minutes">Timeout <input id="ai-max-time" type="number" value="3" min="1" max="30" step="1" onchange="aiAgent._applyLimits()"> min</label>
                    <div style="flex:1"></div>
                    <span id="ai-step-counter"></span>
                    <span id="ai-token-counter"></span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Collapsible config panel -->
            <div id="ai-config-panel" class="ai-config-panel">
                <div class="ai-config-inner">
                    <div class="ai-config-topbar">
                        <span class="ai-config-title">API Settings</span>
                        <button class="ai-config-close-btn" onclick="toggleAthenaConfig(false)" title="Close API settings" aria-label="Close API settings">
                            <svg class="ai-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                                <path d="M4 4L12 12M12 4L4 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                            </svg>
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ai-config-row">
                        <label class="ai-config-label">Provider</label>
                        <select id="ai-provider-select" class="ai-config-select" onchange="aiAgent.selectProvider(true)" title="Provider">
                            <option value="">Select...</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>
                    <div id="ai-provider-compliance-note" class="ai-provider-note" style="display:none"></div>
                    <div class="ai-config-row">
                        <label class="ai-config-label">API Key</label>
                        <div class="ai-key-input-wrap">
                            <input type="password" id="ai-api-key" class="ai-config-input" placeholder="Paste your key..." autocomplete="off" title="API Key" oninput="aiAgent.onApiKeyInput()">
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm ai-key-use-btn" onclick="aiAgent.useLoadedValidatedKey()" title="Use previously verified loaded key">Use Loaded Key</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ai-config-row">
                        <label class="ai-config-label">Model</label>
                        <select id="ai-model-select" class="ai-config-select" onchange="aiAgent._onModelChange()" title="Model">
                            <option value="" disabled selected>Select model...</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ai-config-row" id="ai-custom-model-row" style="display:none">
                        <label class="ai-config-label">Custom ID</label>
                        <input type="text" id="ai-model-custom" class="ai-config-input" placeholder="Custom model ID...">
                    </div>
                    <div id="ai-model-fetch-status" class="ai-model-fetch-status" style="display:none"></div>
                    <div class="ai-config-actions">
                        <button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" onclick="saveAgentConfig()">Save Configuration</button>
                        <button class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary" onclick="aiAgent.exportProfilesJson()" title="Download profiles and API keys as JSON">Export JSON</button>
                        <button class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary" onclick="aiAgent.openProfilesImportPicker()" title="Load profiles and API keys from JSON">Import JSON</button>
                        <input type="file" id="ai-profiles-import-input" accept=".json,application/json" style="display:none" onchange="aiAgent.importProfilesFromFile(this)">
                        <span id="agent-config-status" class="cfg-status"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div id="ai-model-info" class="ai-config-model-info" style="display:none"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </aside>
    <div id="ai-public-cert-modal" class="modal-overlay ai-public-cert-modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="ai-public-cert-title" aria-describedby="ai-public-cert-desc">
        <div class="modal-box ai-public-cert-box">
            <div class="ai-public-cert-head">
                <h3 id="ai-public-cert-title">Public Info Only Certification</h3>
                <button type="button" class="ai-public-cert-close" id="ai-public-cert-close-btn" aria-label="Close">
                    <svg class="ai-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                        <path d="M4 4L12 12M12 4L4 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                    </svg>
                </button>
            </div>
            <p id="ai-public-cert-desc" class="ai-public-cert-text"></p>
            <div class="ai-public-cert-alert">
                <svg class="ai-inline-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M8 2.2L14 13H2Z" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
                    <path d="M8 5.8V9.2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                    <circle cx="8" cy="11.3" r="0.8" fill="currentColor"></circle>
                </svg>
                <div>
                    <strong>No official or CUI data allowed.</strong>
                    <div>Only proceed if this project folder contains public information only.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ai-public-cert-files">
                <div class="ai-public-cert-files-head">
                    <strong>Project file review required</strong>
                    <span id="ai-public-cert-file-count"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="ai-public-cert-files-note">
                    Every file listed below must be public-only. If any file contains official data, CUI, or sensitive operational information, stop and use a CUI-compliant provider.
                </div>
                <ol id="ai-public-cert-file-list" class="ai-public-cert-file-list"></ol>
            </div>
            <label class="ai-public-cert-label" for="ai-public-cert-name">Type your full name as your signature</label>
            <input id="ai-public-cert-name" class="ai-public-cert-input" type="text" autocomplete="name" placeholder="First Last">
            <label class="ai-public-cert-check">
                <input type="checkbox" id="ai-public-cert-ack">
                <span id="ai-public-cert-ack-text">I reviewed every file listed above and certify none contain official data, CUI, or sensitive operational information.</span>
            </label>
            <div id="ai-public-cert-error" class="ai-public-cert-error" style="display:none"></div>
            <div class="ai-public-cert-actions">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary" id="ai-public-cert-cancel-btn">Cancel</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-warning" id="ai-public-cert-confirm-btn" disabled>Sign & Continue</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Help actions moved inline into nav tabs (see #help-actions inside #myTab) -->

    <div class="modal fade" id="checkpoint-manager-modal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="checkpoint-manager-modal-label"
        aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog modal-xl modal-dialog-scrollable">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <div class="modal-header">
                    <h5 class="modal-title" id="checkpoint-manager-modal-label">Checkpoint Manager</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-body">
                    <div class="row g-2 align-items-end mb-3">
                        <div class="col-md-9">
                            <label for="checkpoint-description-input" class="form-label small mb-1">Description</label>
                            <input id="checkpoint-description-input" class="form-control"
                                placeholder="Example: Before adding export and filter panel">
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-3 d-grid">
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="checkpoint-save-btn">Save Checkpoint</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="table-responsive">
                        <table class="table table-dark table-striped table-sm align-middle mb-0">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th style="width: 180px;">Time</th>
                                    <th style="width: 220px;">Files Changed</th>
                                    <th>Description</th>
                                    <th class="text-end" style="width: 170px;">Actions</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody id="checkpoint-table-body">
                                <tr>
                                    <td colspan="4" class="text-center text-muted">No checkpoints yet.</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    <small id="checkpoint-modal-status" class="d-block mt-2"></small>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="modal fade" id="quick-prompts-modal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="quick-prompts-modal-label"
        aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-centered">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <div class="modal-header">
                    <h5 class="modal-title" id="quick-prompts-modal-label">Quick Prompt</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-body">
                    <p id="quick-prompt-description" class="mb-2"></p>
                    <div id="quick-prompt-request-wrap">
                        <label for="quick-prompt-request" class="form-label small mb-1">What do you want AI to do?</label>
                        <textarea id="quick-prompt-request" class="form-control mb-2" rows="6"
                            placeholder="Describe your request in plain language."></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div id="quick-prompt-debug-fields" style="display:none;">
                        <label for="quick-prompt-debug-description" class="form-label small mb-1">Describe the bug in plain language</label>
                        <textarea id="quick-prompt-debug-description" class="form-control mb-2" rows="4"
                            placeholder="Example: Clicking Save does nothing after I add a new row."></textarea>
                        <label for="quick-prompt-debug-errors" class="form-label small mb-1">Dev console errors (paste exact output)</label>
                        <textarea id="quick-prompt-debug-errors" class="form-control mb-2" rows="5"
                            placeholder="Paste console errors here. If there are none, write: No console errors shown."></textarea>
                        <small class="d-block mb-2">To capture errors: press <strong>F12</strong>, open <strong>Console</strong>, reproduce the bug, then copy red error text. If you are on NMCI and the normal console is blocked, use your loaded <strong>DevConsole.js</strong> tool and paste those errors instead.</small>
                        <div id="quick-prompt-devconsole-cta" class="mb-2" style="display:none;">
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-info" id="quick-prompt-add-devconsole">Add DevConsole.js to Project</button>
                            <small class="d-block mt-1">This creates <strong>devconsole.js</strong> and injects it into your HTML files.</small>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-check mb-2" id="quick-prompt-new-chat-wrap" style="display:none;">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="quick-prompt-new-chat" checked>
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="quick-prompt-new-chat">
                            New conversation (append codebase)
                        </label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-2" id="quick-prompt-entrypoint-wrap" style="display:none;">
                        <label for="quick-prompt-entrypoint" class="form-label small mb-1">Codebase entry point</label>
                        <select id="quick-prompt-entrypoint" class="form-select form-select-sm"></select>
                    </div>
                    <small id="quick-prompt-note" class="d-block mb-1"></small>
                    <small id="quick-prompt-status" class="d-block"></small>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="quick-prompt-generate-btn">Generate + Copy Prompt</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="modal fade" id="advanced-incorporate-modal" tabindex="-1"
        aria-labelledby="advanced-incorporate-modal-label" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-centered">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <div class="modal-header">
                    <h5 class="modal-title" id="advanced-incorporate-modal-label">Incorporate Feature</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-body">
                    <p id="advanced-incorporate-description" class="mb-2"></p>
                    <label for="advanced-incorporate-context" id="advanced-incorporate-context-label"
                        class="form-label small mb-1"></label>
                    <textarea id="advanced-incorporate-context" class="form-control mb-2" rows="5"></textarea>
                    <div class="form-check mb-2" id="advanced-incorporate-new-chat-wrap">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="advanced-incorporate-new-chat" checked>
                        <label class="form-check-label" for="advanced-incorporate-new-chat">
                            New conversation (append codebase)
                        </label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-2" id="advanced-incorporate-entrypoint-wrap" style="display:none;">
                        <label for="advanced-incorporate-entrypoint" class="form-label small mb-1">Codebase entry point</label>
                        <select id="advanced-incorporate-entrypoint" class="form-select form-select-sm"></select>
                    </div>
                    <small id="advanced-incorporate-note" class="d-block mb-2"></small>
                    <div class="btn-row mb-2">
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="advanced-incorporate-generate-btn">Generate + Copy Prompt</button>
                    </div>
                    <small id="advanced-incorporate-status" class="d-block mb-2"></small>
                    <div id="advanced-incorporate-output" class="prompt-output bg-dark p-3 rounded"
                        style="font-family: monospace; white-space: pre-wrap; min-height: 80px;"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="modal fade" id="security-explainer-modal" tabindex="-1"
        aria-labelledby="security-explainer-modal-label" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog modal-xl modal-dialog-scrollable">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <div class="modal-header">
                    <h5 class="modal-title" id="security-explainer-modal-label">Security Explainer: Why Forge Apps Are Secure</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-body">
                    <div class="security-explainer-card">
                        <div class="security-explainer-kicker"><strong>Mobile Code</strong> is governed under SC-18 in the host ATO boundary</div>
                        <p class="mb-2">Forge apps are mobile code, compiled for offline browser execution with no required server, no database, and no app-hosted API surface. That removes by default automated interconnects common to normal web systems.</p>
                        <p class="mb-2">Forge adds defense-in-depth controls at compile and runtime: restrictive security headers, URL/form/link hardening, iframe isolation with a mediated bridge for sensitive operations, and verification artifacts.</p>
                        <p class="mb-0">For RMF: treat this under <strong>SC-18 Mobile Code</strong> and host-system controls. The host browser is the authorized system boundary; the HTML/JS file is managed as mobile code executed inside that boundary. <strong>The browser maintains the ATO, not the html file application.</strong></p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="security-explainer-card">
                        <h6>Mobile Code Categories</h6>
                        <ul class="mb-2">
                            <li>Offline HTML/JavaScript in an approved, STIG-compliant browser with network egress blocked is treated as <strong>Category 3 (generally acceptable)</strong>.</li>
                            <li>Category 3 is acceptable specifically because execution is constrained by the browser and does not permit unmediated host-service access.</li>
                            <li>Category 2 examples (such as VBA/Excel macros) need additional safeguards and tighter enterprise policy controls.</li>
                        </ul>
                     </div>

                    <div class="security-explainer-card">
                        <h6>How the Internet Model Maps to Forge</h6>
                        <ol class="mb-2">
                            <li><strong>Request:</strong> Your computer asks for a website.</li>
                            <li><strong>Delivery:</strong> A server sends HTML/CSS/JS files.</li>
                            <li><strong>Execution:</strong> Your browser runs those files locally.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p class="mb-2">In normal web use, your computer asks a server for a site, the server sends HTML/CSS/JS files, and your browser executes those files locally. If you go to facebook.com on your government computer, an unknown server is sending you html/js/css files that are then executing on your government-supplied computer. We accept this because html/css/js is category 3 mobile code run in a secure browser.</p>
                        <p class="mb-2">Forge follows that same browser execution model, but the files are already on your computer instead of being pulled at runtime from a server you may not trust.</p>
                        <p class="mb-0">That means the security emphasis is on local code control and verification in the approved browser boundary, rather than trusting unknown remote server-delivered content.</p>
                    </div>


	                                         <div class="security-explainer-card">
	                        <h6>ATO Boundary: Why This Is Different From a Traditional Web App</h6>
	                        <p class="mb-2">Traditional web-app ATOs focus heavily on server-side and platform concerns: web server hardening, database security, API authz/authn, transport protections, cloud boundary controls, patching, secrets management, and backend monitoring.</p>
	                        <p class="mb-2">Forge offline apps intentionally do not include that architecture. There is no required server runtime, no app database service, and no internet-facing endpoint for the app itself. That removes large portions of conventional attack surface and associated control burden.</p>
	                        <p class="mb-0">What remains is mobile-code governance in the authorized host environment: SC-18 definitions, host/browser baseline, and local execution safeguards.</p>
	                    </div>
	
	                    <div class="security-explainer-card">
	                        <h6>SharePoint Enclave Pattern (SPFx Hosting)</h6>
	                        <p class="mb-2">When your program treats its SharePoint tenant/site as an approved enterprise enclave, Forge can compile for that boundary without opening broad internet egress.</p>
	                        <p class="mb-2">In SharePoint/SPFx compatibility mode, Forge keeps security headers and the isolated runtime wrapper/bridge, then allowlists only <code>'self'</code> plus the configured SharePoint origin in <code>connect-src</code>.</p>
	                        <p class="mb-2">SharePoint API traffic is mediated through a parent-shell proxy bridge for the configured SharePoint origin, rather than broad child-frame network egress.</p>
	                        <p class="mb-0">Result: the compiled app can use approved SharePoint API routes (including SharePoint-style query parameters) while non-allowlisted external origins remain denied unless explicitly approved.</p>
	                    </div>
	
	                    <div class="security-explainer-card">
	                        <h6>Why Category 3 Offline Browser Apps Are Safer Than Category 2 Excel/VBA</h6>
	                        <table class="security-explainer-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Security Dimension</th>
                                    <th>Offline Forge App (Category 3 pattern)</th>
                                    <th>Excel/VBA Macro (Category 2 pattern)</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>System access model</td>
                                    <td>Browser-constrained execution with mediated access to privileged host APIs.</td>
                                    <td>Richer host interaction potential and broader automation capability inside office/runtime context.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Default network posture</td>
                                    <td>Offline-first with CSP/guard controls designed to suppress outbound calls and URL leakage.</td>
                                    <td>Often relies on enterprise macro policy and trust/signing controls; network interactions can still exist by design.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Exfil pathway surface</td>
                                    <td>Browser/web exfil routes are blocked or sanitized at compile/runtime layers.</td>
                                    <td>Macro-enabled document workflows can expose more channels if host controls are weak or bypassed.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Deployment architecture risk</td>
                                    <td>No required web server/database tier for app operation.</td>
                                    <td>Typically part of broader office/email/share workflows with larger enterprise integration surface.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Assurance artifacts</td>
                                    <td>Forge provides built-in security review/testing outputs and deterministic packaging artifacts.</td>
                                    <td>Assurance often depends on external scanning/governance tooling and organizational macro controls.</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>

	                    <div class="security-explainer-card">
	                        <h6>What Forge Actually Does to Secure Apps (Control Inventory)</h6>
	                        <ol class="mb-0">
	                            <li><strong>Restrictive CSP injection</strong>: default deny model with <code>default-src 'none'</code>, <code>connect-src 'none'</code> by default (or explicit API allowlist), <code>form-action 'none'</code>, <code>frame-src 'none'</code>, <code>object-src 'none'</code>, and <code>manifest-src 'none'</code>.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Header hardening</strong>: adds <code>Referrer-Policy: no-referrer</code>, <code>X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff</code>, <code>Permissions-Policy</code>, and DNS prefetch suppression.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Link-hint neutralization</strong>: runtime strips/neutralizes risky <code>&lt;link rel&gt;</code> hints with browser-dependent CSP behavior (for example prefetch/prerender-like paths).</li>
	                            <li><strong>URL/query hardening</strong>: runtime sanitizes navigation targets and strips query strings by default; only approved mail compose params (<code>subject</code>, <code>body</code>, <code>cc</code>, <code>bcc</code>) are retained for <code>mailto:</code>. In SharePoint compatibility mode, query params are allowed for the configured SharePoint origin only.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Form exfil controls</strong>: sanitizes form actions and blocks GET submissions that leak data in URLs.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Embedded content controls</strong>: sanitizes <code>iframe/frame/embed src</code>, <code>object data</code>, and <code>srcdoc</code>; strips meta refresh navigation patterns.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Dynamic DOM enforcement</strong>: MutationObserver continually re-sanitizes newly inserted or mutated attributes.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Isolated execution shell</strong>: compiled app runs inside sandboxed iframe; sensitive actions are mediated by parent-shell bridge, not directly by untrusted app script.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Gesture-gated capability bridge</strong>: directory/file picker and related host actions require explicit user approval events.</li>
	                            <li><strong>First API-call approval gate</strong>: for non-SharePoint allowlisted API origins, the host shell prompts for explicit user permission before outbound API calls are allowed.</li>
	                            <li><strong>SharePoint whitelist bridge mode</strong>: with SharePoint compatibility enabled, bridge logic pre-allows only the configured SharePoint origin, routes SharePoint <code>fetch</code> traffic through the parent-shell proxy, and blocks non-allowlisted destinations.</li>
	                            <li><strong>SharePoint context seeding for iframe/srcdoc hosts</strong>: runtime seeds <code>_spPageContextInfo</code> into the child app so SharePoint context detection remains stable in nested iframe deployments.</li>
	                            <li><strong>Integrity and evidence outputs</strong>: manifest/hashes and security testing workflows support auditability and reproducibility.</li>
	                        </ol>
	                    </div>

                    <div class="security-explainer-card">
                        <h6>MITRE ATT&amp;CK-Informed Threat Mapping (Vectors and Forge Response)</h6>
                        <table class="security-explainer-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>ATT&amp;CK Vector (Enterprise)</th>
                                    <th>How It Appears in This Modality</th>
                                    <th>Forge Mitigation</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>User execution / malicious content launch</td>
                                    <td>User opens a crafted local HTML app.</td>
                                    <td>Sandboxed runtime + strict CSP + navigation/form/URL guards limit post-execution abuse.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Command and script execution in app context</td>
                                    <td>Injected JS tries to run exfil or loader logic.</td>
                                    <td><code>connect-src</code> default-deny (or explicit API allowlist), blocked embed/object/frame surfaces, and sanitized navigation routes reduce viable execution outcomes.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Exfiltration over web/network protocols</td>
                                    <td>fetch/XHR/WebSocket/beacon attempts to remote endpoint.</td>
                                    <td>CSP network denial and runtime link/form guard layers shut down common outbound channels.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Data staged in URL/query for leakage</td>
                                    <td>App appends sensitive state to links/forms/window.open.</td>
                                    <td>Query stripping, GET form blocking, and mailto allow-list enforcement.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Defense evasion through browser edge primitives</td>
                                    <td>Use of link hints, meta refresh, base tag mutation, srcdoc navigation tricks.</td>
                                    <td>Dedicated runtime neutralization/sanitization for those non-deterministic pathways.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Privilege escalation via host capabilities</td>
                                    <td>Script attempts direct privileged API use (file pickers/open).</td>
                                    <td>Parent bridge mediation with explicit user-gesture approvals and constrained action set.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Supply chain compromise via external dependencies</td>
                                    <td>Runtime CDN/resource tampering.</td>
                                    <td>Inline packaging option + hash/manifest evidence reduces runtime dependency trust.</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>


                    <div class="security-explainer-card security-reference-list">
                        <h6>Official Documentation Quotes (Verbatim)</h6>
                        <p class="mb-2"><strong>NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5, SC-18 Control:</strong> "Define acceptable and unacceptable mobile code and mobile code technologies; and authorize, monitor, and control the use of mobile code within the system."</p>
                        <p class="mb-2"><strong>NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5, SC-18 Discussion:</strong> "Category 3 [mobile code] includes Shockwave Flash content, PDF, and VBScript and ECMAscript-variant scripting languages [javascript] interpreted within the confines of a browser."</p>
                        <p class="mb-2"><strong>CNSSI No. 1253, SC-18 (category criteria):</strong> "Category 3 mobile code having limited functionality, with no capability for unmediated access to workstation, server, and remote system services and resources may be used when executing in an approved browser."</p>
                        <ul class="mt-2 mb-0">
                            <li><a href="https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/GOVPUB-C13-PURL-LPS72075/pdf/GOVPUB-C13-PURL-LPS72075.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NIST Mobile Code</a></li>
                            <li><a href="https://rmf.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/CNSSI_1253_2022.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CNSSI</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="security-explainer-card security-reference-list">
                        <h6>Recommended Governance Language (Paste Into Policy Drafts)</h6>
                        <p class="mb-2">"Offline HTML/JavaScript applications compiled by Forge may be authorized as constrained mobile code under SC-18 organizational definitions when executed in an approved browser baseline with network egress controls and host/platform STIG compliance. They do not introduce a server or database tier; risk treatment therefore focuses on host execution controls, integrity evidence, and continuous verification."</p>
                    </div>

                </div>
